createSpecialCell(uint256,uint8,address).details: Create a new CELL token in the Grid, with specific properties This special cell may be immediately transferred to a specific owner This function should only be called very rarely (giveaway competitions etc.)

params._initialTeam: - ID of the new CELL's team
params._owner: - Address of the new CELL's owner
params._properties: - A predefined properties string for the CELL

discoverCell().details: 'Discover' (create) a new CELL token (tile) on The Grid, spiraling outwards from [0,0] Discovered CELL tokens are immediately put up for auction The auction price decreases over 7 days, unless it was in the first 225 tiles, which have fixed prices

getCellData(uint256).details: Get the properties of a given Cell

getGridTokenCirculatingSupply().details: Calculate the number of circulating GRID tokens The token contract calculates all minted tokens minus all sent to the burn address Here we also subtract any minted but unclaimed tokens from that total

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

mineGridTokens(uint8[8]).details: Mint new tokens and calculate distributions to each team based on their representation on the grid

params._sortedTeamOrder: - The sorted array of teams based on their current grid representation ranking - arrays are sorted off-chain and passed as an input to avoid gas costs, - but are verified on chain to ensure data matches contract values (thus avoiding any manipulation) - team rankings changing between when order is calculated off and on chain will cause a revert
